parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal can cause extended stopping distances, accidents, or loss of control, leading to potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the brake pedal is hard to press
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the vehicle accelerates instead of stopping
the vehicle slides or locks up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake rotors can cause vibrations, noise, and reduced braking performance, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Grinding noise
squeaking noise
vibration when braking
reduced braking performance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hydraulic system can cause extended stopping distances, accidents, or loss of control, leading to potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the brake pedal is hard to press
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the vehicle accelerates instead of stopping.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the occupants of the vehicle are not properly protected.
symptoms: Airbags fail to deploy in a crash
resulting in injuries or fatalities to the occupants.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The deployment of airbags at low speeds can cause unnecessary injuries to the occupants, as well as unnecessary repair costs.
symptoms: Airbags deploy at low speeds
causing injuries to the occupants.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag warning light can lead to a lack of awareness of potential airbag system faults, which can increase the risk of injury or fatality in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The airbag warning light fails to illuminate
indicating a potential fault in the airbag system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden acceleration can cause loss of control of the vehicle, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly
making it difficult to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake failure can cause loss of control of the vehicle, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The brakes fail to respond
making it difficult to stop the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to jerk, lose power, or slip out of gear, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission makes noise
acts strange
jerks
loses power
slips out of gear
or fails to hold the vehicle in place on inclines.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fifth gear can cause the transmission to pop out of gear, leading to a loss of momentum and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The transmission pops out of fifth gear
requiring the driver to physically hold the stick in place to maintain speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake light switch can cause the brake lights to malfunction, leading to accidents or increasing the risk of rear-ending.
symptoms: The brake lights do not work
and the transmission cannot be shifted out of park.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the driveshaft can cause the vehicle to stop suddenly, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The driveshaft freezes
causing the vehicle to stop
accompanied by a knocking sound from the universal joints.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch assembly can cause the vehicle to lose power or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
or the clutch fails to engage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the shift lock can cause the vehicle to become inoperable, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The shift lock jams
preventing any operation of the vehicle.
